This article is a proclamation by President Barack Obama declaring May 9, 2010, as Mother's Day in the United States. The proclamation acknowledges the hard work and selflessness of mothers throughout generations and their impact on shaping America's character. It mentions the efforts of Julia Ward Howe and Anna Jarvis in establishing a day to honor mothers. The proclamation emphasizes the role of mothers in protecting and nurturing their children, and their contributions to leadership, compassion, and service in the country. It also recognizes the various forms of nurturing families and the different types of mothers. The proclamation concludes by urging Americans to express their love and gratitude to their mothers and to remember those who have passed away but continue to inspire.